From: Oleksandr Natalenko <oleksandr@natalenko.name>
Subject: [pf-curated-6.6] ksm: process_ksm_{enable,disable,status} syscalls + KSM mm hooks

Re-cut from natalenko's pf-kernel branch ksm-6.6 (tip d7c6cf799aba)
as a single bulk diff, restricted to the files this overlay's curation
kept on the 6.6 LTS slot. Source: codeberg.org/pf-kernel/linux.

Three new syscalls (process_ksm_enable / process_ksm_disable /
process_ksm_status) at numbers 453-455 across all architectures —
evolved from 6.1's single pmadv_ksm syscall into a more granular
control surface. Touches arch/*/syscalls/syscall*.tbl plus the MM-side
hooks in include/linux/ksm.h and include/uapi/linux/prctl.h.
---
